Before running this application, ensure you have the following installed on your machine:

Node.js: Download and Install Node.js

Getting Started

To set up and run this project locally, follow these steps:

1. Clone the Repository:

git clone https://github.com/Atirek-Srivastava/quiz-app.git
Navigate to the Project Directory:

2. cd quiz

3. Install Dependencies:

npm install
This will install all the required dependencies specified in the package.json file.

4. Start the Application: node app.js
   This will start the Node.js server.

5. Access the Application: Open your web browser and navigate to http://localhost:3000 to use the quiz application.

Project Structure

The project structure is as follows:

app.js: Main entry point of the application.
public/: Directory containing static files (HTML, CSS, client-side JavaScript).
data/questions.json: JSON file containing quiz questions and answers.
views/: Directory containing server-side views (if applicable).
Customization
You can customize the quiz questions by modifying the questions.json file in the data/ directory.

